      "created_at": null,
      "html_url": "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/commit/abf89ded8f6c8fc742ee79b13835b30ef9e2bada",
      "tree": {
        "sha": "72fe90156e40dab8ca1b5418a671a0ea3f09f69e",
        "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/git/trees/72fe90156e40dab8ca1b5418a671a0ea3f09f69e"
      },
      "verification": {
        "verified": true,
        "reason": "valid",
        "payload": "tree 72fe90156e40dab8ca1b5418a671a0ea3f09f69e\nparent ff7cdf633e375f151cccbcc78c7add161b3d29b8\nauthor will <will@256k1.dev> 1773656372 +0000\ncommitter will <will@256k1.dev> 1773658647 +0000\n\nci: Use arch-appropriate mlc binary in lint install\n\nReplace the hardcoded x86_64 binary name with $(uname -m) so the\ncorrect mlc binary is downloaded when building the lint container\nfor non-x86_64 architectures (e.g. aarch64).\n\nIf the arch is not one of aarch64-linux or x86_64-linux, fallback to x64\nbins to avoid (download) failures in cases where running non-native\nbinaries currently works, like with qemu binfmt.\n",
